"
Earlier this week, Nick Cave cancelled a performance in Russia due to the war and announced that he "stands with Ukraine and prays that the madness will end soon."
In doing so, the esteemed Australian singer joined artists and bands like Iggy Pop, Green Day, and Franz Ferdinand, who also cancelled performances in the invading country.
But in the case of Kiev, his cancellation notice took a slightly different turn.
