Those involved in the issue argue that the failure to enforce the price is due, among other things, to a lack of detention facilities and the fact that arrests are only made when there are accompanying offenses or in the case of a recidivist.
Legal experts argue that the decision to charge a fee from the detainee only from the third arrest was made, among other things, because the courts cannot cope with the number of arrests made every day.
Whoever checks the punishment as well, will discover that it is not deterrent.
There is a great complexity.
